<br>
If you have too few points coming in, nobody can ever afford anything.<br>
<br>
If you have too few points going out, it leads to point hoarding.<br>
<br>
When Cult of Setekh was setting up it's DKP system, I was concerned about point hoarding (it had been a problem in Soveriegn's Might), so I, along with my officers, delayed the introduction for several weeks until we had a chance to run tests.<br>
<br>
In the end, the system worked very well. Any given member could expect to recieve an upgrade in turn, and nothing ever rotted.<br>
<br>
When demand for loot from certain mobs started to drop off, we would devalue the mob's point value (NEVER adjust the value of items unless the mob that drops it is a new addition to your target list. Otherwise, it can lead to &quot;but x-person only paid 4 points, why should I pay 5?&quot;) until the mob would reach a value of 0.0 and we would stop persuing it.<br>
<br>
My guild is gone now, but one thing I think you will find everyone agreed on was that we were extremely fair with our loot distribution. My only regret was not finding more loot for our chain classes, particularly our Rogues. <p>Thedosius Dreamtwister<br>
