On the other hand, it's prefereable to the random system, which always rewards the underequipped player (who rolls on everything, probably beating out the well equipped player on the one time a month something drops he could use).  Random leads to a very even equipment level in your guild, what is not always the best for a raid oriented build (that needs a MT, high mana regen clerics etc).<br>
Award loot systems are the ones that best help your guild progress - and most easily destroy your guild.  Nothing worse then people getting the feeling &quot;loot only goes to friends of XYZ&quot;.  The best way to handle award is probably to keep your own hidden dkp, but use it only as a guildeline when determening where to put the loot (aka if it's not guild-important, reward attendance, if it is, screw dkp, the MT needs that BoC). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=260848">Shamu Whitewale</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
