<br>
If you plan to go on and get into higher and higher stuff all the time, then i strongly suggest a DKP system. The earlier you start it, the better. I am not sure where you are in the game, but if you start doing HoT, this might be a good time to also start such a number based system. <br>
<br>
The system will help you to distribute loot somewhat fair. In the beginning people wont like it, but they ll soon realize its actually not that bad, especially if you assign loot already instead to roll.<br>
<br>
The system will help you to decide who gets what, which will be very helpful when 100hp/100mana All/All items start to drop and every class claims it fits best for just this class.<br>
<br>
Of course there are guilds out there which assign loot by some council, but if you arent a leading guild or ALL very close friends (which i doubt) then this wont work out for you.<br>
<br>
When using DKP you can choose between open and closed numbers. Both things have ups and downs. I suggest closed numbers to avoid discussions. Determinging values for items is very hard and the less people are involved in that the better. Its important however to watch that your DKP in = DKP out and adjust values over time to accomodate that.<br>
<br>
